pageContext.claim: “MEXICO HAS AGREED TO IMMEDIATELY BEGIN BUYING LARGE QUANTITIES OF AGRICULTURAL PRODUCT FROM OUR GREAT PATRIOT FARMERS!”
pageContext.analysis: Mexico is already the second largest market for agricultural goods from the United States and Mexico's foreign minister said this claim about the border deal was untrue. "There is no agreement of any kind," Marcelo Ebrard said on June 10. "It is an immigration agreement. There’s no commercial [element] in this document."
